Interface AuthenticationInjection<Target>

    public interface AuthenticationInjection<Target>
extends Injection<Target>
    Injects a key store based authentication into some target.

      • algorithm

        AuthenticationInjection<Target> algorithm(String algorithm)
        Sets the name of the signature algorithm (optional). If this method is not called, then the same algorithm is used which has been used to sign the public key in the entry.
        Returns:
        this

      • keyProtection

        AuthenticationInjection<Target> keyProtection(PasswordProtection keyProtection)
        Sets the password protection which is used for accessing the private key in the key entry (optional). A private key entry is only required to generate license keys, that is for any vendor license manager and for any consumer license manager for a free trial period. If this method is not called then the key store protection is used.
        Returns:
        this

        AuthenticationInjection<Target> loadFrom(Source source)
